Two people have been arrested in connection with the murder of Knysna councillor, Victor Molosi. Police Minister Bheki Cele announced this at his funeral on Saturday. Molosi was gunned down in front of his house last month. Cele noted that police were pursuing two more suspects. Many moving tributes were given. Molosi was described as a family man who was civic minded. The family want the guilty brought to justice. Molosi leaves behind his wife Nomonde and four sons. WATCH BELOW: 